scopia  wikipedia scopia from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search not to be confused with skopje scopia within the computer networking and telecommunications fields is a series of unified communications products that provide meetme videoconferencing and online collaboration the scopia products include the scopia xt telepresence scopia xt room system supporting also the h standard scopia xt room system scopia xt room system scopia xt meeting center room system scopia firewall traversal multipoint control units gateways scopia control scopia desktop video conferencing and scopia mobile hd video conferencing the scopia products are developed and sold by avaya and their business partner network contents  history  xt room systems  awards  xt room system  desktop and mobile  gateways  see also  references  further reading  external links historyedit on  april  shareholders approved the acquisition of radvision by avaya for about  million plans were announced in june to integrated radvision products with the avaya aura unified communication systems xt room systemsedit the scopia xt is a unified communication video conferencing system with many video conferencing endpoint options the system is capable of dual pfps live video content hd audio h scalable video coding svc along with ipad multitouch control the xt system also automatically scales bandwidth in unpredictable network environments during the video conferencing the scopia xt systems include the  advanced telecommunications computing architecture atca carrier grade systems  and  systems and the xt systems    and  awardsedit editor’s choice award for achievement in  from industry analyst telepresence and videoconferencing insight newsletter  frost  sullivan new product innovation award  jitc certified xt room systemedit high definition video communications the features include pfps live video and content hd audio h high profile and scalable video coding dual display support and a wide angle pan–tilt–zoom ptz camera desktop and mobileedit the desktop software is compatible with both microsoft windows and mac systems and works with the web browsers internet explorer firefox safari and google chrome the system uses h and sip standards to interoperate with other video conferencing systems scalable video coding insures performance over congested networks without affecting other users scopia content slider allows the scopia desktop user can go back to the previous slides during a presentation scopia mobile allows hd video conferencing from mobile devices such as the ipad iphone ipod and android wireless connection speeds over cell systems varies greatly and netsense optimizes the conference session as it monitors the connection quality dynamically changing from hd video to whatever the connection can support as needed gatewaysedit isdn gateway tip gateway microsoft gateway see alsoedit videoconferencing list of video telecommunication services and product brands referencesedit  radvision acquired by avaya radvision retrieved  sep    shoshanna solomon  march  avaya agrees to acquire radvision for about  million business week retrieved  june    larry hettick  june  one acquisition closes another agreement opens network world retrieved  june    madhubanti rudra  april  radvision introduces video conferencing system tmc net retrieved  june    a b radvision an avaya company earns frost  sullivan new product innovation award for video conferencing  telepresence endpoints  radvision chosen as videoenabled unified communications company of the year by industry analyst telepresence and videoconferencing insight global investor  feb  retrieved  sep    the radvision scopia xt  the industrys most powerful video system in its class the street  jan  retrieved  sep    david s maldow radvision an avaya company earns frost  sullivan new product innovation award for video conferencing  telepresence endpoints telepresence options retrieved  septe   check date values in accessdate help  extension of the special interoperability test certification of the radvision scopia pdf defense information systems agency  jan  retrieved  sep    radvision video conferencing solution receives uc apl certification from us federal government tmc net business wire  july  retrieved  sep    user guide for scopia elite  series mcu version  pdf p  retrieved  sep    radvision debuts two new vtc systems rave publications  april  retrieved  sep    scopia xt  a b tpvc insight technical panel  feb  review radvision scopia desktop retrieved  sep  scopia desktop is ‘standards based’ with h and sip interoperability this means that users can connect with the widest range of roombased video conferencing systems and can have a tandberg cisco polycom and lifesize end point in their scopia desktop meeting if needed offering excellent compatibility   vincent chavy  june  scopia desktop  points of success retrieved  sep    scopia mobile conference with your mobile device  lee h badman  oct  radvision does bigtime smalldevice video conferencing network computing retrieved  sep   further readingedit getting started with scopia desktop – university of maryland pdf university of maryland retrieved  sep   scopia desktop installation research and education advanced network new zealand retrieved  sep   running scopia videoconferencing from windows pdf vanderbilt university school of nursing retrieved  sep   scopia desktop university of west florida retrieved  sep   external linksedit radvision scopia desktop and mobile applications radvision scopia video conferencing infrastructure radvision scopia® xt video conferencing v t e avaya products routers and switches vsp  series vsp  series vsp  series vsp  series ers  series ers  series ers  series ers  series ers  series ers  series security devices secure router  secure network access nac vpn router ip phones  series ip deskphones e e sa avaya  series ip deskphones protocols shortest path bridging spb auto detection auto configuration fast stacking nortel discovery protocol simple loop prevention protocol mlt dmlt smlt dsmlt rsmlt ist pbt ipvpn lite vlacp unistim servers as cs cse csm software and systems agile communication environment communications manager unified communications management enterprise switch manager proactive voice quality management scopia retired products a key system definity merlin other avaya government solutions tenovis wellfleet communications category commons retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlescopiaoldid categories avayaweb conferencingvideotelephonyteleconferencinghidden categories cs errors dates navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagespermanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport create a bookdownload as pdfprintable version languages add links this page was last edited on  april  at  text is available under the creative commons attributionsharealike license additional terms may apply by using this site you agree to the terms of use and privacy policy wikipedia® is a registered trademark of the wikimedia foundation inc a nonprofit organization privacy policy about wikipedia disclaimers contact wikipedia developers cookie statement mobile view scopia  wikipedia scopia from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search not to be confused with skopje scopia within the computer networking and telecommunications fields is a series of unified communications products that provide meetme videoconferencing and online collaboration the scopia products include the scopia xt telepresence scopia xt room system supporting also the h standard scopia xt room system scopia xt room system scopia xt meeting center room system scopia firewall traversal multipoint control units gateways scopia control scopia desktop video conferencing and scopia mobile hd video conferencing the scopia products are developed and sold by avaya and their business partner network contents  history  xt room systems  awards  xt room system  desktop and mobile  gateways  see also  references  further reading  external links historyedit on  april  shareholders approved the acquisition of radvision by avaya for about  million plans were announced in june to integrated radvision products with the avaya aura unified communication systems xt room systemsedit the scopia xt is a unified communication video conferencing system with many video conferencing endpoint options the system is capable of dual pfps live video content hd audio h scalable video coding svc along with ipad multitouch control the xt system also automatically scales bandwidth in unpredictable network environments during the video conferencing the scopia xt systems include the  advanced telecommunications computing architecture atca carrier grade systems  and  systems and the xt systems    and  awardsedit editor’s choice award for achievement in  from industry analyst telepresence and videoconferencing insight newsletter  frost  sullivan new product innovation award  jitc certified xt room systemedit high definition video communications the features include pfps live video and content hd audio h high profile and scalable video coding dual display support and a wide angle pan–tilt–zoom ptz camera desktop and mobileedit the desktop software is compatible with both microsoft windows and mac systems and works with the web browsers internet explorer firefox safari and google chrome the system uses h and sip standards to interoperate with other video conferencing systems scalable video coding insures performance over congested networks without affecting other users scopia content slider allows the scopia desktop user can go back to the previous slides during a presentation scopia mobile allows hd video conferencing from mobile devices such as the ipad iphone ipod and android wireless connection speeds over cell systems varies greatly and netsense optimizes the conference session as it monitors the connection quality dynamically changing from hd video to whatever the connection can support as needed gatewaysedit isdn gateway tip gateway microsoft gateway see alsoedit videoconferencing list of video telecommunication services and product brands referencesedit  radvision acquired by avaya radvision retrieved  sep    shoshanna solomon  march  avaya agrees to acquire radvision for about  million business week retrieved  june    larry hettick  june  one acquisition closes another agreement opens network world retrieved  june    madhubanti rudra  april  radvision introduces video conferencing system tmc net retrieved  june    a b radvision an avaya company earns frost  sullivan new product innovation award for video conferencing  telepresence endpoints  radvision chosen as videoenabled unified communications company of the year by industry analyst telepresence and videoconferencing insight global investor  feb  retrieved  sep    the radvision scopia xt  the industrys most powerful video system in its class the street  jan  retrieved  sep    david s maldow radvision an avaya company earns frost  sullivan new product innovation award for video conferencing  telepresence endpoints telepresence options retrieved  septe   check date values in accessdate help  extension of the special interoperability test certification of the radvision scopia pdf defense information systems agency  jan  retrieved  sep    radvision video conferencing solution receives uc apl certification from us federal government tmc net business wire  july  retrieved  sep    user guide for scopia elite  series mcu version  pdf p  retrieved  sep    radvision debuts two new vtc systems rave publications  april  retrieved  sep    scopia xt  a b tpvc insight technical panel  feb  review radvision scopia desktop retrieved  sep  scopia desktop is ‘standards based’ with h and sip interoperability this means that users can connect with the widest range of roombased video conferencing systems and can have a tandberg cisco polycom and lifesize end point in their scopia desktop meeting if needed offering excellent compatibility   vincent chavy  june  scopia desktop  points of success retrieved  sep    scopia mobile conference with your mobile device  lee h badman  oct  radvision does bigtime smalldevice video conferencing network computing retrieved  sep   further readingedit getting started with scopia desktop – university of maryland pdf university of maryland retrieved  sep   scopia desktop installation research and education advanced network new zealand retrieved  sep   running scopia videoconferencing from windows pdf vanderbilt university school of nursing retrieved  sep   scopia desktop university of west florida retrieved  sep   external linksedit radvision scopia desktop and mobile applications radvision scopia video conferencing infrastructure radvision scopia® xt video conferencing v t e avaya products routers and switches vsp  series vsp  series vsp  series vsp  series ers  series ers  series ers  series ers  series ers  series ers  series security devices secure router  secure network access nac vpn router ip phones  series ip deskphones e e sa avaya  series ip deskphones protocols shortest path bridging spb auto detection auto configuration fast stacking nortel discovery protocol simple loop prevention protocol mlt dmlt smlt dsmlt rsmlt ist pbt ipvpn lite vlacp unistim servers as cs cse csm software and systems agile communication environment communications manager unified communications management enterprise switch manager proactive voice quality management scopia retired products a key system definity merlin other avaya government solutions tenovis wellfleet communications category